'''Gneiskopf Peak''' ({{Coord|71|56|S|12|07|E|}}) is a peak ({{convert|2930|m|disp=or}}) rising {{convert|5|mi|0}} southwest of [[Mount Neustruyev]] at the southern end of [[SÃ¼dliche Petermann Range]], in the [[Wohlthat Mountains]] of [[Queen Maud Land]].
==Discovery and naming== Gneiskopf Peak was discovered and given the descriptive name Gneiskopf (gneiss peak) by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938-1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]].<ref>[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/ USGS GNIS: Gneiskopf Peak]</ref>
